WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:24.200
الحمد بالله رب العالمين الرحمن الرحيم مالك يوم الدين إياك نعبد وإياك نستعيم إهدن الصراة المستقيم صراة الذين أنعنت عليهم غير المرضوب عليهم

00:00:24.200 --> 00:00:35.660
السلام عليكم ورحمة الله وبركاته

00:00:35.660 --> 00:00:47.260
بسم الله الرحمن الرحيم الحمد لله وحده وصلى الله وسلم وبارك على من لا نبي بعده وعلى آله وأصحابه والتابعين ومن تابعهم بإحسان إلى يوم الدين

00:00:47.260 --> 00:01:16.260
بسم الله الرحمن الرحيم

00:01:16.260 --> 00:01:31.460
Beloved brothers and sisters in Islam, the nation of the Muslims in Madinah al-Munawwara had been built on the foundations of goodness and piety.

00:01:31.460 --> 00:01:37.160
The Masjid had been built, the first one upon piety known as Masjid Quba.

00:01:37.160 --> 00:01:47.360
Thereafter the second Masjid to be built was Al-Masjid al-Nabawi or Masjid Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم within Madinah al-Munawwara.

00:01:47.360 --> 00:01:55.660
These are the blessed Masjid built by the most blessed of hands, the hands of Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم.

00:01:55.660 --> 00:02:03.160
He took part in building the Masjid and this is why it is a Sunnah of Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:02:03.160 --> 00:02:11.160
not only to contribute towards the building of Masjid but to take a moment to pick a brick or two up with your own hand and lay it.

00:02:11.160 --> 00:02:16.860
May Allah سبحانه وتعالى grant us goodness, this is also the Sunnah of Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم.

00:02:16.860 --> 00:02:23.860
We are so weak that in our lives we can only fulfill a few of the Sunnah of Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم.

00:02:23.860 --> 00:02:32.560
Whereas there are hundreds of thousands of Sunnah, we as ordinary human beings would be unable to fulfill all of them

00:02:32.560 --> 00:02:39.060
and this is why do not belittle what someone else is doing thinking that you are the only one serving Islam.

00:02:39.060 --> 00:02:44.360
Perhaps they are also engaging in a Sunnah and by you saying I am the only one serving Islam,

00:02:44.360 --> 00:02:51.760
you would be insulting the Sunnah of Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم which is far broader than just one or two things.

00:02:51.760 --> 00:02:55.160
May Allah سبحانه وتعالى grant us a deep understanding of the Deen

00:02:55.160 --> 00:02:59.160
and may He make us from amongst those who can support one another.

00:02:59.160 --> 00:03:09.160
As we ended off yesterday making mention of the points that Nabi صلى الله عليه وسلم had stressed whilst he was in Majina Munawwara at the beginning.

00:03:09.160 --> 00:03:16.160
These were firstly I made mention of the issue of education to the degree that as I said after the war,

00:03:16.160 --> 00:03:27.860
after one of the wars, he actually issued an instruction to those who were captive saying that if you can teach ten from amongst us to read and write, we will free you.

00:03:27.860 --> 00:03:37.860
This was the importance given to education by Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم and on top of that the importance of a good upbringing,

00:03:37.860 --> 00:03:45.860
the importance of good character and conduct, cleansing of the heart, ridding it of hatred, malice, jealousy and so on

00:03:45.860 --> 00:03:52.860
and ridding it of any of the bad qualities, this tazkiyah to nafs and meaning purification of the heart,

00:03:52.860 --> 00:04:02.860
something very very important that every single one of us needs to consider and needs to engage in in fact because with us we are human beings

00:04:02.860 --> 00:04:12.860
and we are not from amongst the Anbiya of Allah سبحانه وتعالى who were protected by Allah سبحانه وتعالى, safeguarded by Allah سبحانه وتعالى.

00:04:12.860 --> 00:04:17.860
We are ordinary human beings, Shaytan comes to us and tries to divert us.

00:04:17.860 --> 00:04:28.860
So Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم constantly reminded his companions to cleanse their hearts, to remove hatred, to remove malice, jealousy of one another and so on

00:04:28.860 --> 00:04:39.860
and above that to love one another and the brotherhood should always remain, these were some of the prime teachings of Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:04:39.860 --> 00:04:46.860
over and above worshipping Allah سبحانه وتعالى and obeying the instruction of the messenger.

00:04:46.860 --> 00:04:57.860
So as this happened, let's take a look at some of the first ahadith of Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم memorized in Al Madinatul Munawwarah.

00:04:57.860 --> 00:05:08.860
These were words that came out of his blessed mouth صلى الله عليه وسلم and they were put into practice, they were taken very very seriously.

00:05:08.860 --> 00:05:13.860
As I go through these words, remember these are the words that built the nation.

00:05:13.860 --> 00:05:23.860
Let's, every one of us, look into ourselves how close or far we are from the same words and we will be able to see whether we are good

00:05:23.860 --> 00:05:33.860
or whether we are just from amongst those who pay lip service to the Deen saying that you know I follow Islam but in actual fact we are following something very far from Islam.

00:05:33.860 --> 00:05:38.860
So the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم says when he was asked

00:05:38.860 --> 00:05:45.860
Which of Islam is the best? Now this question means what is the best thing I could do as a Muslim?

00:05:45.860 --> 00:05:57.860
And the answer came several times in different wordings all heading towards one conclusion and every time a different point was raised

00:05:58.860 --> 00:06:00.860
And on this occasion he says

00:06:06.860 --> 00:06:15.860
He says to feed food to whom? Starting with the poor, those who are poor, those who are in need, those who are hungry.

00:06:15.860 --> 00:06:20.860
We will come to another hadith just now inshallah which clarifies this as well from another angle.

00:06:20.860 --> 00:06:27.860
Feed food to people, be considerate about people and spread salaam, the greeting as well as peace.

00:06:27.860 --> 00:06:34.860
Spread the greeting to those whom you know as well as those whom you don't know.

00:06:34.860 --> 00:06:38.860
That's a very important point. Today point number one we lack.

00:06:38.860 --> 00:06:47.860
We'll greet but we only greet when there is a maslaha or when there is something for ourselves that we find we might want to gain from this person.

00:06:47.860 --> 00:06:56.860
If there is a person down prodden who perhaps we fear he might ask us for a thing or two, we start off by turning away and we don't even greet.

00:06:56.860 --> 00:07:02.860
We greet people inshallah because of their wealth. This is what has come nowadays. Sometimes this happens.

00:07:02.860 --> 00:07:14.860
We greet people because of their status but we leave those whom perhaps had we greeted them the acceptance from Allah would have been far greater than having greeted the whole community of wealthy people.

00:07:14.860 --> 00:07:19.860
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala forgive us. So this is the importance of salaam.

00:07:19.860 --> 00:07:26.860
To those you know to those you don't know. The fact that they are muslimin they deserve the greeting.

00:07:26.860 --> 00:07:30.860
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala make us from amongst those who understand.

00:07:30.860 --> 00:07:36.860
So at that time the muhajireen and ansar they knew that these are from the ansar these are from the muhajireen.

00:07:36.860 --> 00:07:42.860
But initially they had to be acquainted with one another and they had to get to know one another.

00:07:42.860 --> 00:07:47.860
And this is why salaam was important to everyone. You know them you don't know them you greet them.

00:07:47.860 --> 00:07:50.860
They have a link with Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:07:50.860 --> 00:07:56.860
Another hadith he says la yadkhulul jannata man la ya'man ja'uhu bawa'iqa.

00:07:56.860 --> 00:08:06.860
Amazing. He will not enter paradise whose neighbors are not protected from his harm.

00:08:07.860 --> 00:08:12.860
Amazing. This was building Madina Munawwara so the neighbors were looked towards.

00:08:12.860 --> 00:08:17.860
One narration says when you are making some stew add a little bit more in it to give the neighbors.

00:08:17.860 --> 00:08:24.860
Subhanallah. With us never mind giving the neighbor something good we give them something bad.

00:08:24.860 --> 00:08:30.860
May Allah protect us. It happens. Let us hope that we can be from amongst those who don't do that.

00:08:30.860 --> 00:08:32.860
And we can be from amongst those who understand.

00:08:32.860 --> 00:08:40.860
The powerful words he will not enter paradise whose neighbor is not safe from his harm because that is your neighbor.

00:08:40.860 --> 00:08:48.860
And if each one has to fulfill this the whole community will be people who fulfill the rights of one another because we are all neighbors of someone.

00:08:49.860 --> 00:08:52.860
Another narration. Powerful words.

00:08:57.860 --> 00:09:05.860
A Muslim is a person whom all the Muslims are protected from the harms of his tongue or his hand.

00:09:05.860 --> 00:09:10.860
Look at the powerful words. Today we are in an age of rumor and gossip.

00:09:10.860 --> 00:09:21.860
It becomes so juicy that the marination of the chicken that we happen to bribe or to put on the fire barbecue chicken that marination is left one side.

00:09:21.860 --> 00:09:27.860
The juiciness of the statements of rumor about our own brothers and sisters is far greater.

00:09:27.860 --> 00:09:33.860
In Ramadan in the condition of fast and rumors are flying and Vodacom has made it quite easy to do that.

00:09:33.860 --> 00:09:37.860
May Allah protect us. Allah safeguard us. Wallahi we need to be careful.

00:09:37.860 --> 00:09:49.860
A true Muslim is he whom all the Muslims are safeguarded from the evil of his tongue and his hand which means physical harm or verbal harm.

00:09:49.860 --> 00:09:56.860
Not at all. It goes deeper than that. We are not even supposed to be holding ill feeling in our heart for one another.

00:09:56.860 --> 00:09:58.860
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:09:58.860 --> 00:10:05.860
If there is something people are engaged in that is bad we should try and talk to them directly and try and help them and so on.

00:10:05.860 --> 00:10:11.860
And if there is something that we cannot do anything about we can at least make a good prayer, feel it in our hearts that this is wrong.

00:10:11.860 --> 00:10:21.860
But we don't need to go around spreading tale, rumor and gossip because what happens to a person who spreads rumor it comes back to haunt him at some stage later on.

00:10:21.860 --> 00:10:24.860
May Allah protect us. And this is one thing we don't realize.

00:10:24.860 --> 00:10:31.860
Sometimes we suffer in life without knowing that it is the result of a rumor we spread about a friend of Allah.

00:10:31.860 --> 00:10:36.860
And this thing came back to us to haunt us and our lives are upside down and we don't even know.

00:10:36.860 --> 00:10:39.860
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us.

00:10:39.860 --> 00:10:44.860
These were the building stones of the foundation of this nation and another hadith.

00:10:44.860 --> 00:10:46.860
The Prophet salallahu alayhi wa sallam says

00:10:51.860 --> 00:10:56.860
None of you are true believers until you love for your brother what you love for yourself.

00:10:56.860 --> 00:10:59.860
So you love goodness for yourself you should love it for others.

00:10:59.860 --> 00:11:02.860
You want everything to be good for you you should want it for them.

00:11:02.860 --> 00:11:07.860
And you should make dua for them or wherever you can and you are able you should help them.

00:11:07.860 --> 00:11:10.860
Open the doors for them and Allah will open your doors.

00:11:10.860 --> 00:11:12.860
This is why the hadith says

00:11:15.860 --> 00:11:17.860
The true believers are like one man.

00:11:17.860 --> 00:11:20.860
If his eye is sore his whole body is restless.

00:11:20.860 --> 00:11:24.860
If his hand one organ is paining his whole body will be restless.

00:11:24.860 --> 00:11:27.860
These are the words of the Prophet Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:11:27.860 --> 00:11:30.860
In another narration of a similar meaning he says

00:11:35.860 --> 00:11:42.860
A believer his relation with another believer is like that of a wall of a building.

00:11:42.860 --> 00:11:44.860
Each brick strengthens the other.

00:11:44.860 --> 00:11:48.860
Without one you find the whole wall or the whole building is weak.

00:11:48.860 --> 00:11:54.860
So we need to hold each other up and we need to make sure we stand as a wall as a building.

00:11:54.860 --> 00:11:56.860
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:11:56.860 --> 00:11:57.860
Then he says

00:12:01.860 --> 00:12:02.860
In one narration he says

00:12:05.860 --> 00:12:08.860
Do not be jealous of one another.

00:12:08.860 --> 00:12:11.860
Do not hold hatred against one another.

00:12:11.860 --> 00:12:13.860
Don't turn away from one another.

00:12:13.860 --> 00:12:16.860
These are the building stones of the foundation.

00:12:16.860 --> 00:12:22.860
The building stones within the nation of Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:12:22.860 --> 00:12:25.860
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to grant us acceptance.

00:12:25.860 --> 00:12:29.860
And he says you should be brothers for the sake of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:12:29.860 --> 00:12:31.860
Worshippers of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:12:31.860 --> 00:12:35.860
Then something very important he says

00:12:35.860 --> 00:12:41.860
Whoever spends time is spending time helping his brother.

00:12:41.860 --> 00:12:45.860
Allah will be helping him for that period of time.

00:12:45.860 --> 00:12:46.860
And another narration

00:12:46.860 --> 00:12:57.860
Allah continues to help a person for as long as that person is engaged in helping his brother.

00:12:57.860 --> 00:12:58.860
Subhanallah.

00:12:58.860 --> 00:12:59.860
Look at this.

00:12:59.860 --> 00:13:01.860
So people began to help one another.

00:13:01.860 --> 00:13:02.860
They loved one another.

00:13:02.860 --> 00:13:04.860
They opened their doors for one another.

00:13:04.860 --> 00:13:05.860
They were feeding one another.

00:13:05.860 --> 00:13:07.860
They had a good feeling for one another.

00:13:07.860 --> 00:13:10.860
When they had problems or crises they would resolve it immediately.

00:13:10.860 --> 00:13:12.860
The hadith continues to say

00:13:12.860 --> 00:13:16.860
Whoever removes a Muslim from a difficulty of the dunya

00:13:16.860 --> 00:13:21.860
Allah will remove him from the difficulty of the akhirah and the day of judgement when he needs it more.

00:13:21.860 --> 00:13:23.860
Subhanallah.

00:13:23.860 --> 00:13:26.860
We sometimes create problems for people.

00:13:26.860 --> 00:13:27.860
Forget about removing them.

00:13:27.860 --> 00:13:28.860
It's a fact.

00:13:28.860 --> 00:13:31.860
This is why you find degradation of the nation.

00:13:31.860 --> 00:13:33.860
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us.

00:13:33.860 --> 00:13:34.860
Then he says

00:13:34.860 --> 00:13:38.860
Whoever covers the faults of a Muslim, of a believer

00:13:38.860 --> 00:13:42.860
Allah will cover his faults on the day of judgement.

00:13:42.860 --> 00:13:43.860
Look at this.

00:13:43.860 --> 00:13:46.860
Today we each to expose people.

00:13:46.860 --> 00:13:48.860
Because that is the western thinking, the idea.

00:13:48.860 --> 00:13:50.860
The minute you see something, announce it to the world.

00:13:50.860 --> 00:13:51.860
Go to the press.

00:13:51.860 --> 00:13:52.860
Tell the whole world.

00:13:52.860 --> 00:13:58.860
That is the western idea that everyone should know everything about every single person.

00:13:58.860 --> 00:13:59.860
So what happens?

00:13:59.860 --> 00:14:02.860
The world continues looking at them with an evil eye.

00:14:02.860 --> 00:14:03.860
And who are they to judge?

00:14:03.860 --> 00:14:04.860
Allahu akbar.

00:14:04.860 --> 00:14:06.860
Whereas the Islamic teaching is

00:14:06.860 --> 00:14:07.860
You see something wrong.

00:14:07.860 --> 00:14:08.860
You don't go and expose.

00:14:08.860 --> 00:14:09.860
You resolve the matter.

00:14:09.860 --> 00:14:12.860
If you love a person, see something wrong.

00:14:12.860 --> 00:14:14.860
You don't go and start telling the whole world.

00:14:14.860 --> 00:14:15.860
You go to them and you say

00:14:15.860 --> 00:14:17.860
My brother, this is something that was wrong.

00:14:17.860 --> 00:14:18.860
Please rectify it.

00:14:18.860 --> 00:14:19.860
I am your brother.

00:14:19.860 --> 00:14:20.860
I care for you.

00:14:20.860 --> 00:14:22.860
And then if the whole world sees something wrong,

00:14:22.860 --> 00:14:24.860
You don't go and start telling the whole world.

00:14:24.860 --> 00:14:25.860
You go to them and you say

00:14:25.860 --> 00:14:27.860
My brother, this is something that was wrong.

00:14:27.860 --> 00:14:28.860
Please rectify it.

00:14:28.860 --> 00:14:30.860
And then if the person rectifies it,

00:14:30.860 --> 00:14:33.860
You are brothers in Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala's love.

00:14:33.860 --> 00:14:36.860
And the two of you will be resurrected together

00:14:36.860 --> 00:14:39.860
As those who love each other for the sake of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:14:39.860 --> 00:14:44.860
Granted a special place on the day of Qiyamah, the day of judgment.

00:14:44.860 --> 00:14:47.860
So this is of extreme importance and we learn a lot from it.

00:14:47.860 --> 00:14:51.860
And we learn how today we have different thinking

00:14:51.860 --> 00:14:53.860
Because of the environment we live in

00:14:53.860 --> 00:14:56.860
And we have this love of exposure of people

00:14:56.860 --> 00:14:58.860
And we think that there is goodness in it

00:14:58.860 --> 00:15:01.860
Not realizing that if Allah were to expose us,

00:15:01.860 --> 00:15:03.860
None of us would be seated here this evening.

00:15:03.860 --> 00:15:04.860
Allah akbar

00:15:04.860 --> 00:15:06.860
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala forgive us

00:15:06.860 --> 00:15:09.860
And may He cover us in the dunya as well as in the akhirah.

00:15:09.860 --> 00:15:12.860
Then He says the powerful words

00:15:12.860 --> 00:15:14.860
Irhamu man fil ardi

00:15:14.860 --> 00:15:16.860
Yarhamkum man fil sama

00:15:16.860 --> 00:15:18.860
Have mercy upon those on earth

00:15:18.860 --> 00:15:20.860
And the one in the skies will have mercy upon you

00:15:20.860 --> 00:15:23.860
Meaning Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala will have mercy upon you.

00:15:23.860 --> 00:15:25.860
Imagine these words.

00:15:25.860 --> 00:15:27.860
The Jewish people are listening to them.

00:15:27.860 --> 00:15:29.860
The mushriks are listening to them.

00:15:29.860 --> 00:15:31.860
And at the time of Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:15:31.860 --> 00:15:34.860
The ansar and muhajireen are learning from them.

00:15:34.860 --> 00:15:36.860
And they become merciful, compassionate.

00:15:36.860 --> 00:15:40.860
Their hearts open up and soften up at the same time.

00:15:40.860 --> 00:15:47.860
Then He says a mu'min is not one who eats to his fill

00:15:47.860 --> 00:15:50.860
Whilst his neighbor is hungry.

00:15:50.860 --> 00:15:51.860
Look at that.

00:15:51.860 --> 00:15:53.860
Words of Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:15:54.860 --> 00:15:56.860
Then He says

00:15:56.860 --> 00:15:58.860
One of the levels of Iman

00:15:58.860 --> 00:16:03.860
Is to remove a harmful object from the path of people.

00:16:03.860 --> 00:16:04.860
Amazing.

00:16:04.860 --> 00:16:07.860
You drive your vehicle, you notice a brick in the middle of the road

00:16:07.860 --> 00:16:08.860
Between you and Allah

00:16:08.860 --> 00:16:11.860
If you were to stop your vehicle, ensuring safety obviously

00:16:11.860 --> 00:16:14.860
And you were to spend a moment to remove that brick

00:16:14.860 --> 00:16:16.860
Solely between you and Allah

00:16:16.860 --> 00:16:19.860
It's a sign of Iman and belief in your maker.

00:16:19.860 --> 00:16:22.860
Because you would not like fellow human beings

00:16:22.860 --> 00:16:25.860
To be harmed by something you saw.

00:16:25.860 --> 00:16:27.860
Perhaps they may not see it.

00:16:27.860 --> 00:16:30.860
May Allah sallallahu alaihi wa sallam grant us protection.

00:16:30.860 --> 00:16:32.860
And in this way you may never know

00:16:32.860 --> 00:16:36.860
How many times you were saved from being harmed

00:16:36.860 --> 00:16:39.860
By something on the path because of others

00:16:39.860 --> 00:16:41.860
Before you who removed the object.

00:16:41.860 --> 00:16:43.860
Before you even came here.

00:16:43.860 --> 00:16:44.860
Allahu Akbar

00:16:44.860 --> 00:16:46.860
May Allah sallallahu alaihi wa sallam grant us goodness.

00:16:46.860 --> 00:16:50.860
And this is why the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wa sallam says

00:16:50.860 --> 00:16:52.860
Be careful.

00:16:52.860 --> 00:16:55.860
Be careful of those two types of people who are cursed.

00:16:55.860 --> 00:16:58.860
Who are they O Messenger sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:16:58.860 --> 00:16:59.860
He says

00:17:02.860 --> 00:17:06.860
The one who relieves himself

00:17:06.860 --> 00:17:08.860
Upon the path of people.

00:17:08.860 --> 00:17:11.860
Where people walk, they relieve themselves there.

00:17:11.860 --> 00:17:14.860
So now there is a stench and a smell, they are cursed.

00:17:14.860 --> 00:17:16.860
These are cursed by the people who walk.

00:17:16.860 --> 00:17:19.860
And at the same time, the others who relieve themselves

00:17:19.860 --> 00:17:21.860
In the resting places of people.

00:17:21.860 --> 00:17:23.860
The shade where people might take a bit of rest.

00:17:23.860 --> 00:17:26.860
And you find you go into the shade and you want to be busy.

00:17:26.860 --> 00:17:28.860
You know you want to lay your picnic for example.

00:17:28.860 --> 00:17:30.860
And there you have a human being before you

00:17:30.860 --> 00:17:32.860
Who has just relieved himself.

00:17:32.860 --> 00:17:34.860
The Messenger sallallahu alaihi wa sallam warns us.

00:17:34.860 --> 00:17:37.860
Imagine today we speak of environmental cleanliness

00:17:37.860 --> 00:17:39.860
And pollution and so on.

00:17:39.860 --> 00:17:42.860
These were beautiful teachings of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:17:42.860 --> 00:17:43.860
The basics.

00:17:43.860 --> 00:17:45.860
And this is what community is based upon.

00:17:45.860 --> 00:17:47.860
Cleanliness and compassion

00:17:47.860 --> 00:17:49.860
And the feeling for one another.

00:17:49.860 --> 00:17:51.860
And this is why he says

00:17:51.860 --> 00:17:55.860
Any Muslim who has clothed another Muslim

00:17:55.860 --> 00:17:57.860
Who did not have clothing.

00:17:57.860 --> 00:18:00.860
Allah will grant them a special clothing

00:18:00.860 --> 00:18:02.860
On the day of Qiyamah and in paradise.

00:18:02.860 --> 00:18:03.860
Subhanallah.

00:18:03.860 --> 00:18:06.860
It means people who are without clothes.

00:18:06.860 --> 00:18:08.860
People who don't have something to cloth themselves.

00:18:08.860 --> 00:18:11.860
If you help them, you get a special clothing

00:18:11.860 --> 00:18:13.860
From Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:18:13.860 --> 00:18:15.860
And anyone who feeds another

00:18:15.860 --> 00:18:17.860
Who is hungry.

00:18:17.860 --> 00:18:19.860
Allah will feed them

00:18:19.860 --> 00:18:21.860
From the food of Jannah.

00:18:21.860 --> 00:18:22.860
Subhanallah.

00:18:22.860 --> 00:18:24.860
The food of paradise.

00:18:24.860 --> 00:18:26.860
So this is not just feeding the wealthy.

00:18:26.860 --> 00:18:28.860
This hadith is specifically

00:18:28.860 --> 00:18:30.860
Feeding those who do not have food.

00:18:30.860 --> 00:18:31.860
Look for them.

00:18:31.860 --> 00:18:32.860
Hunt for them.

00:18:32.860 --> 00:18:33.860
Go and give them

00:18:33.860 --> 00:18:35.860
And Allah prepares for you food.

00:18:35.860 --> 00:18:36.860
Subhanallah.

00:18:36.860 --> 00:18:38.860
And the last part of that hadith it says

00:18:38.860 --> 00:18:41.860
And whosoever quenches the thirst.

00:18:41.860 --> 00:18:44.860
Whosoever quenches the thirst of a person

00:18:44.860 --> 00:18:45.860
Who is thirsty.

00:18:45.860 --> 00:18:47.860
Who doesn't have that drink.

00:18:47.860 --> 00:18:49.860
And whosoever quenches them.

00:18:49.860 --> 00:18:51.860
Allah will grant them a drink.

00:18:51.860 --> 00:18:52.860
From what is known as

00:18:52.860 --> 00:18:53.860
Al-Rahiq Al-Makhtoom.

00:18:53.860 --> 00:18:55.860
Which is the sealed nectar.

00:18:55.860 --> 00:18:57.860
Special drink of paradise.

00:18:57.860 --> 00:18:59.860
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant that to us.

00:18:59.860 --> 00:19:02.860
So these are some of the beautiful narrations

00:19:02.860 --> 00:19:05.860
That were the building point of the nation.

00:19:05.860 --> 00:19:07.860
In Madinatul Munawwara.

00:19:07.860 --> 00:19:09.860
Over and above the treaties.

00:19:09.860 --> 00:19:10.860
And the various agreements

00:19:10.860 --> 00:19:12.860
That we spoke about yesterday.

00:19:12.860 --> 00:19:14.860
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:19:14.860 --> 00:19:15.860
To help us.

00:19:15.860 --> 00:19:18.860
Realize and look into these hadith.

00:19:18.860 --> 00:19:19.860
And many more.

00:19:19.860 --> 00:19:20.860
And ask ourselves.

00:19:20.860 --> 00:19:23.860
How close or far am I

00:19:23.860 --> 00:19:25.860
From these teachings of Islam?

00:19:25.860 --> 00:19:26.860
And if I am far.

00:19:26.860 --> 00:19:29.860
What am I going to do about it?

00:19:29.860 --> 00:19:30.860
Remember as I always say.

00:19:30.860 --> 00:19:32.860
This is the month of Ramadan.

00:19:32.860 --> 00:19:33.860
We have a few more days.

00:19:33.860 --> 00:19:36.860
We have already passed the half way mark.

00:19:36.860 --> 00:19:38.860
If you look at it carefully.

00:19:38.860 --> 00:19:40.860
And when we exit Ramadan.

00:19:40.860 --> 00:19:43.860
Are we going to be from amongst those who exited

00:19:43.860 --> 00:19:46.860
Without having taken anything from it.

00:19:46.860 --> 00:19:49.860
With us as we exit.

00:19:49.860 --> 00:19:51.860
So every goodness we leave it in Ramadan

00:19:51.860 --> 00:19:52.860
And we walk out.

00:19:52.860 --> 00:19:53.860
What was the point?

00:19:53.860 --> 00:19:55.860
We'd rather have the month of Ramadan.

00:19:55.860 --> 00:19:58.860
If it has changed us.

00:19:58.860 --> 00:20:00.860
And it has woken us up.

00:20:00.860 --> 00:20:03.860
And it has made us develop our good qualities.

00:20:03.860 --> 00:20:06.860
And it has made us eradicate our bad qualities.

00:20:06.860 --> 00:20:08.860
Then we have achieved from the month of Ramadan.

00:20:08.860 --> 00:20:09.860
If not.

00:20:09.860 --> 00:20:11.860
We have just wasted our time fasting.

00:20:11.860 --> 00:20:12.860
And standing in Salah.

00:20:12.860 --> 00:20:13.860
As the narration says.

00:20:13.860 --> 00:20:15.860
How many people who fast.

00:20:15.860 --> 00:20:16.860
They achieve nothing.

00:20:16.860 --> 00:20:18.860
Besides hunger and thirst from the fast.

00:20:18.860 --> 00:20:20.860
How many people who stand at night in prayer.

00:20:20.860 --> 00:20:21.860
They achieve nothing.

00:20:21.860 --> 00:20:22.860
Besides getting tired.

00:20:22.860 --> 00:20:23.860
And staying awake.

00:20:23.860 --> 00:20:26.860
May Allah not make us from those.

00:20:26.860 --> 00:20:28.860
May Allah open our doors.

00:20:28.860 --> 00:20:30.860
Let us get back to the situation.

00:20:30.860 --> 00:20:31.860
In Madinatul Munawwara.

00:20:31.860 --> 00:20:32.860
Now Quraish.

00:20:32.860 --> 00:20:34.860
They started understanding.

00:20:34.860 --> 00:20:36.860
And realizing what has happened.

00:20:36.860 --> 00:20:38.860
Makkatul Mukarrama was empty.

00:20:38.860 --> 00:20:40.860
They had no one to poke.

00:20:40.860 --> 00:20:42.860
Basically they had no one to harm.

00:20:42.860 --> 00:20:46.860
They had no one to actually make life difficult for.

00:20:46.860 --> 00:20:48.860
So what did they do?

00:20:48.860 --> 00:20:49.860
They wrote a letter.

00:20:49.860 --> 00:20:50.860
Who should they write to?

00:20:50.860 --> 00:20:53.860
Because now the leader of Madinatul Munawwara.

00:20:53.860 --> 00:20:55.860
Is Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam.

00:20:55.860 --> 00:20:56.860
If you recall.

00:20:56.860 --> 00:20:57.860
We made mention of a man.

00:20:57.860 --> 00:20:59.860
Who was about to be appointed as the leader.

00:20:59.860 --> 00:21:03.860
His name was Abdullah ibn Ubayy ibn Salool.

00:21:03.860 --> 00:21:05.860
Quraish wrote a letter to him.

00:21:05.860 --> 00:21:07.860
And told him few words.

00:21:07.860 --> 00:21:08.860
That look.

00:21:08.860 --> 00:21:11.860
You have given asylum to a wanted man.

00:21:11.860 --> 00:21:13.860
Who is wanted by us.

00:21:13.860 --> 00:21:15.860
If you do not hand him over to us.

00:21:15.860 --> 00:21:18.860
We are coming with a huge army to wipe you out.

00:21:18.860 --> 00:21:20.860
Basically these were the words.

00:21:20.860 --> 00:21:21.860
We are coming with a huge army.

00:21:21.860 --> 00:21:23.860
We are going to fight your men.

00:21:23.860 --> 00:21:25.860
And we are going to enslave and capture your women.

00:21:25.860 --> 00:21:26.860
That's what we are going to do.

00:21:26.860 --> 00:21:29.860
So when Salool got this letter.

00:21:29.860 --> 00:21:31.860
He was very happy in a way.

00:21:31.860 --> 00:21:33.860
Because to him he said.

00:21:33.860 --> 00:21:34.860
Let me make a big noise about it.

00:21:34.860 --> 00:21:37.860
So that I can get Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam out.

00:21:37.860 --> 00:21:40.860
So that I can be the leader once again.

00:21:40.860 --> 00:21:42.860
But as soon as he started making a noise.

00:21:42.860 --> 00:21:43.860
Within certain circles.

00:21:43.860 --> 00:21:45.860
Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam.

00:21:45.860 --> 00:21:48.860
Being informed by Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala.

00:21:48.860 --> 00:21:49.860
What did he do?

00:21:49.860 --> 00:21:52.860
He got up and went to Salool and his people.

00:21:52.860 --> 00:21:53.860
And said.

00:21:53.860 --> 00:21:57.860
You have overreacted regarding the letter that came from Quraish.

00:21:57.860 --> 00:21:58.860
You have overreacted.

00:21:58.860 --> 00:22:00.860
Do not overreact to it.

00:22:00.860 --> 00:22:02.860
This teaches us a lesson.

00:22:02.860 --> 00:22:04.860
Sometimes something small.

00:22:04.860 --> 00:22:05.860
We don't understand.

00:22:05.860 --> 00:22:06.860
We overreact.

00:22:06.860 --> 00:22:08.860
We get very excited about things.

00:22:08.860 --> 00:22:11.860
So we make a mountain as I always say.

00:22:11.860 --> 00:22:12.860
From a little mole hill.

00:22:12.860 --> 00:22:13.860
A big mountain.

00:22:13.860 --> 00:22:14.860
And yet.

00:22:14.860 --> 00:22:16.860
If we had asked those who had had knowledge.

00:22:16.860 --> 00:22:18.860
And we asked those with experience.

00:22:18.860 --> 00:22:19.860
They would tell you.

00:22:19.860 --> 00:22:20.860
Brother just ignore this.

00:22:20.860 --> 00:22:21.860
Don't worry.

00:22:21.860 --> 00:22:22.860
It's minor.

00:22:22.860 --> 00:22:23.860
It's small.

00:22:23.860 --> 00:22:24.860
Just leave it.

00:22:24.860 --> 00:22:25.860
Allahu Akbar.

00:22:25.860 --> 00:22:26.860
We have to face negativity in life.

00:22:26.860 --> 00:22:27.860
No one can say.

00:22:27.860 --> 00:22:29.860
I have a smooth life with no negativity.

00:22:29.860 --> 00:22:30.860
Because then.

00:22:30.860 --> 00:22:31.860
What was the point of Jannah?

00:22:31.860 --> 00:22:32.860
Paradise.

00:22:32.860 --> 00:22:35.860
Paradise is going to be a place where there will only be.

00:22:35.860 --> 00:22:36.860
Positives.

00:22:36.860 --> 00:22:37.860
No negatives.

00:22:37.860 --> 00:22:40.860
If the worldly life was the same.

00:22:40.860 --> 00:22:43.860
Then what was the point of going to paradise?

00:22:43.860 --> 00:22:46.860
May Allah SWT grant us a deeper understanding.

00:22:46.860 --> 00:22:48.860
And so when they wrote this letter.

00:22:48.860 --> 00:22:50.860
And Muhammad SAW then.

00:22:50.860 --> 00:22:54.860
Reacted upon the reaction of Salool.

00:22:54.860 --> 00:22:56.860
Things started coming down.

00:22:56.860 --> 00:22:58.860
But the whispering was still on.

00:22:58.860 --> 00:23:00.860
No you see these people are going to come and attack us.

00:23:00.860 --> 00:23:01.860
In the meantime.

00:23:01.860 --> 00:23:03.860
Something else had happened.

00:23:03.860 --> 00:23:04.860
Sa'ad Ibn Mu'al.

00:23:04.860 --> 00:23:06.860
Who was one of the leaders of Al-Aws.

00:23:06.860 --> 00:23:08.860
As we have made mention of.

00:23:08.860 --> 00:23:09.860
And a Sahabi.

00:23:09.860 --> 00:23:10.860
He went for Umrah.

00:23:10.860 --> 00:23:13.860
And this was the habit of the people at the time.

00:23:13.860 --> 00:23:15.860
Now this man had gone to Makkah Al-Mukarrama.

00:23:15.860 --> 00:23:18.860
And he was a Muslim.

00:23:18.860 --> 00:23:20.860
When he went there.

00:23:20.860 --> 00:23:21.860
Abu Jahl.

00:23:21.860 --> 00:23:24.860
In fact he stayed with Umayyah Ibn Khalaf.

00:23:24.860 --> 00:23:26.860
That was the person whom he stayed with.

00:23:26.860 --> 00:23:28.860
And Umayyah Ibn Khalaf.

00:23:28.860 --> 00:23:30.860
These people used to pass Medina Munawwara.

00:23:30.860 --> 00:23:32.860
On their way to Al-Sham.

00:23:32.860 --> 00:23:34.860
To the northern Arabian region.

00:23:34.860 --> 00:23:37.860
And when they used to take their caravans.

00:23:37.860 --> 00:23:39.860
They used to pass Medina Munawwara.

00:23:39.860 --> 00:23:41.860
And wait for a while.

00:23:41.860 --> 00:23:43.860
And thereafter.

00:23:43.860 --> 00:23:45.860
When Sa'ad Ibn Mu'al went to Makkah Al-Mukarrama.

00:23:45.860 --> 00:23:48.860
As he is making Tawaf.

00:23:48.860 --> 00:23:50.860
Abu Jahl asks him.

00:23:50.860 --> 00:23:52.860
Or asks Umayyah Ibn Khalaf.

00:23:52.860 --> 00:23:53.860
Who is this man?

00:23:53.860 --> 00:23:54.860
He says this is Sa'ad.

00:23:54.860 --> 00:23:55.860
Sa'ad meaning the one from Yathrib.

00:23:55.860 --> 00:23:57.860
The one from Medina.

00:23:57.860 --> 00:23:59.860
He says.

00:23:59.860 --> 00:24:01.860
If you were not with this man.

00:24:01.860 --> 00:24:03.860
I would have stopped you and blocked you.

00:24:03.860 --> 00:24:05.860
You would not have returned back to your people.

00:24:05.860 --> 00:24:07.860
You have given asylum to a wanted man.

00:24:07.860 --> 00:24:09.860
Look at the same statement from the same people.

00:24:09.860 --> 00:24:11.860
Coming again to a different person.

00:24:11.860 --> 00:24:13.860
You have given asylum to a wanted man.

00:24:13.860 --> 00:24:15.860
You have given him a base.

00:24:15.860 --> 00:24:19.860
And you are protecting a person who is wanted.

00:24:19.860 --> 00:24:23.860
We would block you and stop you.

00:24:23.860 --> 00:24:24.860
At this point.

00:24:24.860 --> 00:24:27.860
Sa'ad Ibn Mu'az said very loudly.

00:24:27.860 --> 00:24:30.860
If you try to do anything.

00:24:30.860 --> 00:24:32.860
You will be blocked.

00:24:32.860 --> 00:24:34.860
From going up to Ash-Sham.

00:24:34.860 --> 00:24:35.860
All your caravans.

00:24:35.860 --> 00:24:36.860
We will stop them.

00:24:36.860 --> 00:24:37.860
Block them.

00:24:37.860 --> 00:24:38.860
And you will have to go back.

00:24:38.860 --> 00:24:40.860
Your trade route will be over.

00:24:40.860 --> 00:24:41.860
Closed.

00:24:41.860 --> 00:24:42.860
Your business gone.

00:24:42.860 --> 00:24:43.860
Now they were worried.

00:24:43.860 --> 00:24:45.860
They had to keep quiet once again.

00:24:45.860 --> 00:24:47.860
But they knew that now.

00:24:47.860 --> 00:24:50.860
The Mushriks of Makkah are preparing war.

00:24:50.860 --> 00:24:53.860
Against the believers who are in Medina Munawwara.

00:24:53.860 --> 00:24:56.860
There were many still in Makkah.

00:24:56.860 --> 00:24:58.860
And the Mu'mineen.

00:24:58.860 --> 00:25:00.860
They were not so many.

00:25:00.860 --> 00:25:02.860
There was a head count done.

00:25:02.860 --> 00:25:05.860
Of the people who were able to participate in war.

00:25:05.860 --> 00:25:07.860
If war broke out.

00:25:07.860 --> 00:25:10.860
And 1500 men were counted.

00:25:10.860 --> 00:25:13.860
At that time in Medina Munawwara.

00:25:13.860 --> 00:25:15.860
So that was the population of the men.

00:25:15.860 --> 00:25:18.860
And the boys or should I say the young men.

00:25:18.860 --> 00:25:21.860
And the older people who were fit to fight.

00:25:21.860 --> 00:25:23.860
1500 people.

00:25:23.860 --> 00:25:27.860
And so Quraish knew that they had large numbers.

00:25:27.860 --> 00:25:28.860
But Subhanallah.

00:25:28.860 --> 00:25:31.860
Whilst they were preparing.

00:25:31.860 --> 00:25:34.860
On this side Rasulullah Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam.

00:25:34.860 --> 00:25:37.860
Was visiting different tribes.

00:25:37.860 --> 00:25:39.860
And he was visiting different areas.

00:25:39.860 --> 00:25:41.860
Around Medina Munawwara.

00:25:41.860 --> 00:25:42.860
Signing treaties with the people.

00:25:42.860 --> 00:25:44.860
To say look we are the Muslims.

00:25:44.860 --> 00:25:45.860
We are a nation.

00:25:45.860 --> 00:25:46.860
New nation.

00:25:46.860 --> 00:25:48.860
We are going to protect you.

00:25:48.860 --> 00:25:49.860
If anything happens to you.

00:25:49.860 --> 00:25:51.860
And if an army comes to attack us.

00:25:51.860 --> 00:25:52.860
We will fight together.

00:25:52.860 --> 00:25:53.860
Subhanallah.

00:25:53.860 --> 00:25:55.860
So this was just an agreement.

00:25:55.860 --> 00:25:56.860
That was struck.

00:25:56.860 --> 00:25:59.860
And more and more little groups of people.

00:25:59.860 --> 00:26:01.860
And little clans were joining.

00:26:01.860 --> 00:26:04.860
And more and more areas were joining.

00:26:04.860 --> 00:26:06.860
The Muslim forces.

00:26:06.860 --> 00:26:08.860
In the meantime.

00:26:08.860 --> 00:26:11.860
Something amazing happened.

00:26:11.860 --> 00:26:13.860
The Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam.

00:26:13.860 --> 00:26:16.860
Used to have bodyguards around him.

00:26:16.860 --> 00:26:17.860
The Sahaba radiallahu anhu.

00:26:17.860 --> 00:26:18.860
Did not leave him.

00:26:18.860 --> 00:26:20.860
They had bodyguards around him.

00:26:20.860 --> 00:26:21.860
So much so that.

00:26:21.860 --> 00:26:23.860
Once he speaks about how.

00:26:23.860 --> 00:26:25.860
He had such a good sleep.

00:26:25.860 --> 00:26:28.860
When Sa'd ibn Abi Waqqas radiallahu anhu.

00:26:28.860 --> 00:26:31.860
Was standing guarding him.

00:26:31.860 --> 00:26:34.860
Until Allah revealed verses.

00:26:34.860 --> 00:26:35.860
Where Allah says.

00:26:35.860 --> 00:26:58.860
Oh messenger.

00:26:58.860 --> 00:27:00.860
Get up and convey the message.

00:27:00.860 --> 00:27:02.860
If you don't do so.

00:27:02.860 --> 00:27:04.860
You will not have fulfilled your duty.

00:27:04.860 --> 00:27:08.860
And remember Allah will protect you from the people.

00:27:08.860 --> 00:27:10.860
When those verses were revealed.

00:27:10.860 --> 00:27:12.860
He immediately told those.

00:27:12.860 --> 00:27:13.860
Who used to stand around him.

00:27:13.860 --> 00:27:14.860
You can go away.

00:27:14.860 --> 00:27:16.860
Allah has guaranteed my safety.

00:27:16.860 --> 00:27:17.860
My protection.

00:27:17.860 --> 00:27:18.860
Subhanallah.

00:27:18.860 --> 00:27:20.860
So the hadith in Sahih al-Bukhari.

00:27:20.860 --> 00:27:21.860
Making mention of.

00:27:21.860 --> 00:27:23.860
Those who used to stand around him.

00:27:23.860 --> 00:27:26.860
This was only to the point.

00:27:26.860 --> 00:27:28.860
Where the verses were revealed.

00:27:28.860 --> 00:27:30.860
When Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala revealed verses.

00:27:30.860 --> 00:27:33.860
That I will protect you.

00:27:33.860 --> 00:27:35.860
Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:27:35.860 --> 00:27:38.860
Instructed those who used to stand around him.

00:27:38.860 --> 00:27:39.860
To leave.

00:27:39.860 --> 00:27:40.860
And this is when.

00:27:40.860 --> 00:27:42.860
Sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:27:42.860 --> 00:27:44.860
They knew that he is protected.

00:27:44.860 --> 00:27:46.860
By Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:27:46.860 --> 00:27:48.860
Nothing will ever harm him.

00:27:48.860 --> 00:27:50.860
Except and until.

00:27:50.860 --> 00:27:53.860
The decree of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala has worded.

00:27:53.860 --> 00:27:54.860
So.

00:27:54.860 --> 00:27:57.860
Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:27:57.860 --> 00:27:59.860
At that time.

00:27:59.860 --> 00:28:00.860
Verses were revealed to him.

00:28:00.860 --> 00:28:02.860
Which were very very important.

00:28:02.860 --> 00:28:03.860
Because Quraish.

00:28:03.860 --> 00:28:05.860
They had a bad habit.

00:28:05.860 --> 00:28:07.860
They began to.

00:28:07.860 --> 00:28:09.860
Visit Madina Munawwara quietly.

00:28:09.860 --> 00:28:11.860
And they used to try and inculcate.

00:28:11.860 --> 00:28:13.860
In the hearts and minds of the people.

00:28:13.860 --> 00:28:15.860
That you know this man is like this.

00:28:15.860 --> 00:28:16.860
Like that.

00:28:16.860 --> 00:28:17.860
And they were causing problems.

00:28:17.860 --> 00:28:19.860
On one hand you had.

00:28:19.860 --> 00:28:20.860
Ubayy ibn Salool.

00:28:20.860 --> 00:28:22.860
Abdullah ibn Ubayy ibn Salool.

00:28:22.860 --> 00:28:23.860
He had his group of people.

00:28:23.860 --> 00:28:26.860
They were visiting the mu'mineen and the believers.

00:28:26.860 --> 00:28:28.860
You know those who had believed.

00:28:28.860 --> 00:28:29.860
Newly.

00:28:29.860 --> 00:28:31.860
And they were trying to distract them.

00:28:31.860 --> 00:28:33.860
And find fault in Islam.

00:28:33.860 --> 00:28:34.860
And so on.

00:28:34.860 --> 00:28:35.860
And as for the Jewish people.

00:28:35.860 --> 00:28:36.860
There was a treaty with them.

00:28:36.860 --> 00:28:38.860
But still deep down.

00:28:38.860 --> 00:28:40.860
They used to support Ubayy ibn Salool.

00:28:40.860 --> 00:28:41.860
Anything that happens.

00:28:41.860 --> 00:28:42.860
They would quickly support him.

00:28:42.860 --> 00:28:44.860
So that they tried to create problems.

00:28:44.860 --> 00:28:46.860
In the midst of the Muslims.

00:28:46.860 --> 00:28:48.860
But Allah protected the Muslim.

00:28:48.860 --> 00:28:50.860
And then Allah revealed verses.

00:28:50.860 --> 00:28:52.860
Up to that stage.

00:28:52.860 --> 00:28:54.860
Muslims were not allowed to fight.

00:28:54.860 --> 00:28:56.860
Nor retaliate.

00:28:56.860 --> 00:28:57.860
No revenge.

00:28:57.860 --> 00:28:59.860
And they weren't even allowed to defend.

00:28:59.860 --> 00:29:01.860
If someone had usurped their wealth.

00:29:01.860 --> 00:29:03.860
They had to just go away.

00:29:03.860 --> 00:29:05.860
Up to that point.

00:29:05.860 --> 00:29:07.860
There Allah revealed verses.

00:29:20.860 --> 00:29:22.860
Permission has been granted.

00:29:22.860 --> 00:29:24.860
To those who are being fought.

00:29:24.860 --> 00:29:26.860
To defend themselves.

00:29:26.860 --> 00:29:28.860
And to revenge and retaliate.

00:29:29.860 --> 00:29:31.860
For indeed Allah is all able.

00:29:31.860 --> 00:29:33.860
To grant them victory.

00:29:33.860 --> 00:29:35.860
These verses brought a smile.

00:29:35.860 --> 00:29:37.860
On the faces of the believers.

00:29:37.860 --> 00:29:39.860
Their wealth was usurped.

00:29:39.860 --> 00:29:41.860
Their properties usurped.

00:29:41.860 --> 00:29:42.860
Their people were killed.

00:29:42.860 --> 00:29:44.860
They were driven out of their homes.

00:29:44.860 --> 00:29:47.860
And the mushrik still did not leave them alone.

00:29:47.860 --> 00:29:48.860
They wanted to come to Madina.

00:29:48.860 --> 00:29:49.860
To attack them.

00:29:49.860 --> 00:29:51.860
Now they were granted permission.

00:29:51.860 --> 00:29:52.860
To defend.

00:29:52.860 --> 00:29:54.860
And to revenge.

00:29:54.860 --> 00:29:56.860
Revenge meaning you were booted out.

00:29:56.860 --> 00:29:57.860
You can go back.

00:29:57.860 --> 00:29:58.860
And you can boot them out.

00:29:58.860 --> 00:30:01.860
And you can take back whatever was taken from you.

00:30:01.860 --> 00:30:03.860
Whatever was taken from you, you can take it back.

00:30:03.860 --> 00:30:04.860
And at the same time.

00:30:04.860 --> 00:30:07.860
Anyone tries to harm you now.

00:30:07.860 --> 00:30:09.860
You don't sit back.

00:30:09.860 --> 00:30:10.860
You can actually revenge.

00:30:10.860 --> 00:30:11.860
Subhanallah.

00:30:11.860 --> 00:30:12.860
You can defend yourself.

00:30:12.860 --> 00:30:13.860
And that is the right.

00:30:13.860 --> 00:30:16.860
It's a common right that we have.

00:30:16.860 --> 00:30:19.860
If anyone wants to attack you or me today.

00:30:19.860 --> 00:30:20.860
With whatever I have.

00:30:20.860 --> 00:30:23.860
I need to stand up and make sure I defend myself.

00:30:23.860 --> 00:30:26.860
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us protection.

00:30:27.860 --> 00:30:30.860
So when these verses were revealed.

00:30:32.500 --> 00:30:35.500
Quraysh.

00:30:35.500 --> 00:30:38.500
The Prophet salallahu alaihi wasallam started.

00:30:38.500 --> 00:30:40.500
In an amazing way.

00:30:40.500 --> 00:30:43.500
Finding out information.

00:30:43.500 --> 00:30:45.500
And getting to know the place.

00:30:45.500 --> 00:30:47.500
Getting to know more about Quraysh.

00:30:47.500 --> 00:30:49.500
Preparing to attack.

00:30:49.500 --> 00:30:51.500
Why preparing to attack?

00:30:51.500 --> 00:30:53.500
Very simple.

00:30:53.500 --> 00:30:55.500
This attack was not an attack.

00:30:55.500 --> 00:30:56.500
To spread Islam.

00:30:56.500 --> 00:30:58.500
As people think it was.

00:30:58.500 --> 00:30:59.500
No.

00:30:59.500 --> 00:31:01.500
It was to go back to Quraysh.

00:31:01.500 --> 00:31:03.500
Who killed from amongst us.

00:31:03.500 --> 00:31:05.500
And go back to Quraysh.

00:31:05.500 --> 00:31:07.500
Who had usurped our wealth.

00:31:07.500 --> 00:31:08.500
And our properties.

00:31:08.500 --> 00:31:10.500
And driven us out of our own homes.

00:31:10.500 --> 00:31:12.500
We need to go back.

00:31:12.500 --> 00:31:13.500
And get it.

00:31:13.500 --> 00:31:15.500
Because even the wealth that they have.

00:31:15.500 --> 00:31:17.500
Is contaminated with ours.

00:31:17.500 --> 00:31:19.500
And whatever belonged to us.

00:31:19.500 --> 00:31:20.500
Subhanallah.

00:31:20.500 --> 00:31:22.500
So anytime there were caravans.

00:31:22.500 --> 00:31:23.500
That moved north.

00:31:23.500 --> 00:31:25.500
Towards the Syrian region.

00:31:25.500 --> 00:31:27.500
What was known as Asham.

00:31:27.500 --> 00:31:29.500
It was the right of the Muslims.

00:31:29.500 --> 00:31:31.500
To way lay the caravan.

00:31:31.500 --> 00:31:33.500
And to take every bit of property.

00:31:33.500 --> 00:31:36.500
Because all that belonged to the Muslimin.

00:31:36.500 --> 00:31:38.500
It was usurped from them.

00:31:38.500 --> 00:31:39.500
Subhanallah.

00:31:39.500 --> 00:31:41.500
So this was revenge.

00:31:41.500 --> 00:31:43.500
It was retaliation for what you did.

00:31:43.500 --> 00:31:45.500
For the last 14 years.

00:31:45.500 --> 00:31:48.500
For the last 14 years.

00:31:48.500 --> 00:31:49.500
You harmed us.

00:31:49.500 --> 00:31:50.500
You attacked us.

00:31:50.500 --> 00:31:51.500
You killed us.

00:31:51.500 --> 00:31:52.500
You did this.

00:31:52.500 --> 00:31:53.500
You did that.

00:31:53.500 --> 00:31:55.500
And now we are just allowed to defend.

00:31:55.500 --> 00:31:58.500
So Asham started sending little platoons.

00:31:58.500 --> 00:32:00.500
And reconnaissance missions.

00:32:00.500 --> 00:32:02.500
Of a few of his companions.

00:32:02.500 --> 00:32:04.500
And he sent them into different directions.

00:32:04.500 --> 00:32:07.500
We want to start off making mention of some of them.

00:32:07.500 --> 00:32:09.500
But before I do that.

00:32:09.500 --> 00:32:11.500
Fighting came down in four stages.

00:32:11.500 --> 00:32:12.500
First.

00:32:12.500 --> 00:32:15.500
Only Quraysh were allowed to be fought.

00:32:15.500 --> 00:32:16.500
Nobody else.

00:32:16.500 --> 00:32:19.500
So at this stage when these verses were revealed.

00:32:19.500 --> 00:32:22.500
The Muslims were only allowed to fight Quraysh.

00:32:22.500 --> 00:32:24.500
No one else.

00:32:24.500 --> 00:32:26.500
Then slightly later.

00:32:26.500 --> 00:32:29.500
They were permitted to fight.

00:32:29.500 --> 00:32:31.500
Thereafter the Mushriks from amongst the Arabs.

00:32:31.500 --> 00:32:33.500
Who fought them.

00:32:33.500 --> 00:32:35.500
The Mushriks from amongst the Arabs who fought them.

00:32:35.500 --> 00:32:36.500
And thereafter.

00:32:36.500 --> 00:32:40.500
Anyone who sided with Quraysh in their war.

00:32:40.500 --> 00:32:43.500
Was also fought by the Muslimin.

00:32:43.500 --> 00:32:45.500
Even if they were people of the book.

00:32:45.500 --> 00:32:47.500
Who broke their treaties with the Muslims.

00:32:47.500 --> 00:32:48.500
And the last category.

00:32:48.500 --> 00:32:51.500
Those who started war.

00:32:51.500 --> 00:32:53.500
Anyone who started fighting.

00:32:53.500 --> 00:32:55.500
We were allowed to go back, retaliate.

00:32:55.500 --> 00:32:56.500
And at the same time.

00:32:56.500 --> 00:32:58.500
We could revenge.

00:32:58.500 --> 00:33:00.500
We could fight them preparing an army.

00:33:00.500 --> 00:33:02.500
And go back to attack them.

00:33:02.500 --> 00:33:03.500
Like for example.

00:33:03.500 --> 00:33:04.500
There were instances where.

00:33:04.500 --> 00:33:06.500
The messenger of the Prophet ﷺ.

00:33:06.500 --> 00:33:08.500
Was harmed and was killed.

00:33:08.500 --> 00:33:10.500
He sent a whole army to fight those people.

00:33:10.500 --> 00:33:11.500
Why did you kill our messenger?

00:33:11.500 --> 00:33:12.500
Who are you?

00:33:12.500 --> 00:33:13.500
So you started the war.

00:33:13.500 --> 00:33:14.500
Not us.

00:33:14.500 --> 00:33:15.500
And this is what happened.

00:33:15.500 --> 00:33:17.500
So Rasulullah ﷺ.

00:33:17.500 --> 00:33:19.500
The first platoon that he sent.

00:33:19.500 --> 00:33:21.500
He was not a part of it.

00:33:21.500 --> 00:33:22.500
In Ramadan.

00:33:22.500 --> 00:33:23.500
In the first year of Hijra.

00:33:23.500 --> 00:33:24.500
He sent.

00:33:24.500 --> 00:33:27.500
What is known as Sahriyat Saiful Baha.

00:33:27.500 --> 00:33:31.500
Hamza ibn Abdul Muttalib was sent with 30 men.

00:33:31.500 --> 00:33:33.500
Only to find out information.

00:33:33.500 --> 00:33:35.500
To gather intelligence.

00:33:35.500 --> 00:33:37.500
The idea was to gather intelligence.

00:33:37.500 --> 00:33:38.500
This is what it was.

00:33:38.500 --> 00:33:40.500
These people were not warriors as such.

00:33:40.500 --> 00:33:42.500
The Muslims were calm people.

00:33:42.500 --> 00:33:44.500
But they had to learn.

00:33:44.500 --> 00:33:46.500
And they started gathering information.

00:33:46.500 --> 00:33:49.500
So when Hamza ibn Abdul Muttalib was sent.

00:33:49.500 --> 00:33:51.500
Towards a place known as Saiful Baha.

00:33:51.500 --> 00:33:53.500
With 30 men.

00:33:53.500 --> 00:33:57.500
In order to see and to check.

00:33:57.500 --> 00:33:59.500
The caravan of Abu Jahl.

00:33:59.500 --> 00:34:02.500
That was returning from Ash-Sham.

00:34:02.500 --> 00:34:06.500
That had had 300 strong men.

00:34:06.500 --> 00:34:10.500
So now Hamza ibn Abdul Muttalib went with 30 men.

00:34:10.500 --> 00:34:11.500
As they went.

00:34:11.500 --> 00:34:12.500
They got there.

00:34:12.500 --> 00:34:14.500
They saw the caravan.

00:34:14.500 --> 00:34:17.500
And now the two parties came together.

00:34:17.500 --> 00:34:19.500
And obviously two hostile parties.

00:34:19.500 --> 00:34:21.500
Coming together face to face.

00:34:21.500 --> 00:34:24.500
There was a man known as Majdi ibn Amr.

00:34:24.500 --> 00:34:27.500
And he had had a treaty with both sides.

00:34:27.500 --> 00:34:29.500
So he got up and he said you know what.

00:34:29.500 --> 00:34:30.500
No fighting here.

00:34:30.500 --> 00:34:31.500
We don't want to fight.

00:34:31.500 --> 00:34:32.500
You people go back.

00:34:32.500 --> 00:34:33.500
And you people go back.

00:34:33.500 --> 00:34:34.500
We don't want any war.

00:34:34.500 --> 00:34:35.500
And any fighting.

00:34:35.500 --> 00:34:37.500
So Hamza ibn Abdul Muttalib came back.

00:34:37.500 --> 00:34:39.500
To Al-Madeen Al-Munawwara.

00:34:39.500 --> 00:34:41.500
And Abu Jahl went safely to Makkah Al-Mukarrama.

00:34:41.500 --> 00:34:44.500
But it did something.

00:34:44.500 --> 00:34:45.500
He went back to Makkah.

00:34:45.500 --> 00:34:46.500
And he was worried.

00:34:46.500 --> 00:34:48.500
That these people are brave.

00:34:48.500 --> 00:34:49.500
They are powerful.

00:34:49.500 --> 00:34:53.500
For the first time they are preparing some retaliation.

00:34:53.500 --> 00:34:55.500
So it sent a very strong message.

00:34:55.500 --> 00:34:59.500
Although it was mainly to gather a little bit of intelligence.

00:34:59.500 --> 00:35:02.500
The first flag that was lifted by the Muslimin.

00:35:02.500 --> 00:35:04.500
To see every time there was an army.

00:35:04.500 --> 00:35:06.500
They had had a flag.

00:35:06.500 --> 00:35:08.500
The flags were mainly white.

00:35:08.500 --> 00:35:11.500
So this flag was by Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:35:11.500 --> 00:35:13.500
Given to Hamza radiallahu anhu.

00:35:14.500 --> 00:35:16.500
And he had given it to one of the members of the army.

00:35:16.500 --> 00:35:18.500
It was a white flag.

00:35:18.500 --> 00:35:19.500
It was a little platoon.

00:35:19.500 --> 00:35:21.500
They had gone as we had mentioned.

00:35:21.500 --> 00:35:22.500
Just 30 men.

00:35:22.500 --> 00:35:25.500
The second little skirmish that took place.

00:35:25.500 --> 00:35:27.500
Or we call it a little platoon.

00:35:27.500 --> 00:35:28.500
A sariyah.

00:35:28.500 --> 00:35:30.500
Something, a small reconnaissance mission.

00:35:30.500 --> 00:35:34.500
In order to gather a little bit of intelligence.

00:35:34.500 --> 00:35:38.500
It was what known as sariyat rabegh.

00:35:38.500 --> 00:35:41.500
Which was also in Shawwal in the same year.

00:35:41.500 --> 00:35:43.500
The first year of Hijra.

00:35:43.500 --> 00:35:48.500
And the leader was Ubaidah ibn al-Harif radiallahu anhu.

00:35:48.500 --> 00:35:50.500
He went with 60 men.

00:35:50.500 --> 00:35:54.500
In order to check the caravan of Abu Sufyan.

00:35:54.500 --> 00:35:56.500
That was a much bigger caravan.

00:35:56.500 --> 00:35:58.500
That was coming with 200 men.

00:35:58.500 --> 00:36:00.500
But it had a lot of wealth.

00:36:00.500 --> 00:36:04.500
And it had a lot of merchandise.

00:36:04.500 --> 00:36:06.500
So the two met.

00:36:06.500 --> 00:36:08.500
And they threw spears at each other.

00:36:08.500 --> 00:36:10.500
But this one fled.

00:36:10.500 --> 00:36:12.500
And the other one came back to Madinah al-Munawwara.

00:36:12.500 --> 00:36:14.500
There was no killing as such.

00:36:14.500 --> 00:36:16.500
There were just a few spears and arrows.

00:36:16.500 --> 00:36:19.500
That had flown from one direction to the other.

00:36:19.500 --> 00:36:21.500
And from the other direction to this.

00:36:21.500 --> 00:36:24.500
And from Abu Sufyan's little group of people.

00:36:24.500 --> 00:36:28.500
Two of them came into the Muslim camp.

00:36:28.500 --> 00:36:31.500
And returned to Madinah al-Munawwara.

00:36:31.500 --> 00:36:33.500
They were Muslims already.

00:36:33.500 --> 00:36:35.500
But they had joined the caravan.

00:36:35.500 --> 00:36:37.500
Going on business with the idea.

00:36:37.500 --> 00:36:40.500
Of making the Hijra under cover.

00:36:40.500 --> 00:36:42.500
You see Hijra was not easy.

00:36:42.500 --> 00:36:44.500
So if someone wanted to make Hijra.

00:36:44.500 --> 00:36:46.500
It's like sometimes you know we have.

00:36:46.500 --> 00:36:48.500
Let me give you a simple example.

00:36:48.500 --> 00:36:49.500
Come to my mind now.

00:36:49.500 --> 00:36:51.500
You have for example something going on.

00:36:51.500 --> 00:36:53.500
A religious function going on some way.

00:36:53.500 --> 00:36:56.500
And a person really needs to do a bit of business there.

00:36:56.500 --> 00:36:57.500
Or something.

00:36:57.500 --> 00:36:59.500
And you find a man saying.

00:36:59.500 --> 00:37:01.500
You know what I want to go to the religious function.

00:37:01.500 --> 00:37:02.500
He jumps in.

00:37:02.500 --> 00:37:03.500
He gets a free lift.

00:37:03.500 --> 00:37:04.500
When he goes there.

00:37:04.500 --> 00:37:05.500
He's doing something else.

00:37:05.500 --> 00:37:07.500
This example was the other way round.

00:37:07.500 --> 00:37:09.500
Where these people were going for business.

00:37:09.500 --> 00:37:12.500
And the Muslims two of them jumped in with them.

00:37:12.500 --> 00:37:14.500
Saying that you know what we're coming.

00:37:14.500 --> 00:37:17.500
Not making mention that we want to jump off in Madinah al-Munawwara.

00:37:17.500 --> 00:37:18.500
It so happened.

00:37:18.500 --> 00:37:20.500
That this platoon had met them.

00:37:20.500 --> 00:37:22.500
And they returned with the Muslims.

00:37:22.500 --> 00:37:23.500
Subhanallah.

00:37:23.500 --> 00:37:26.500
The third little platoon that had gone out.

00:37:26.500 --> 00:37:28.500
Sariyat al-Kharrar.

00:37:28.500 --> 00:37:29.500
And that was in Dhul-Qi'da.

00:37:29.500 --> 00:37:31.500
Of the first year of Hijra.

00:37:31.500 --> 00:37:34.500
Sa'd ibn Abi Waqas went with 20 men.

00:37:34.500 --> 00:37:38.500
And he had also aimed for the caravan of Quraysh.

00:37:38.500 --> 00:37:41.500
Why were they aiming for caravans of Quraysh?

00:37:41.500 --> 00:37:42.500
As I said.

00:37:42.500 --> 00:37:44.500
Because that wealth was ours.

00:37:44.500 --> 00:37:47.500
That wealth was contaminated.

00:37:47.500 --> 00:37:49.500
These people stole our wealth.

00:37:49.500 --> 00:37:51.500
They had stolen our properties.

00:37:51.500 --> 00:37:52.500
They had benefited so much.

00:37:52.500 --> 00:37:54.500
They drove us out of our own homes.

00:37:54.500 --> 00:37:57.500
Anything we could get hold of belonged to us.

00:37:57.500 --> 00:37:58.500
They had fought us.

00:37:58.500 --> 00:37:59.500
We need to go back.

00:37:59.500 --> 00:38:02.500
So this is why Sa'd ibn Abi Waqas radiallahu anhu went.

00:38:02.500 --> 00:38:06.500
And as he got to the place that he had supposed to go.

00:38:06.500 --> 00:38:09.500
Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wa sallam told him not to go beyond that.

00:38:09.500 --> 00:38:12.500
So when he got there he found out that the caravan has already passed.

00:38:12.500 --> 00:38:13.500
So he came back.

00:38:13.500 --> 00:38:17.500
But there was another benefit of all these little platoons going out.

00:38:17.500 --> 00:38:20.500
They gathered lots of information about the areas.

00:38:20.500 --> 00:38:21.500
The places.

00:38:21.500 --> 00:38:23.500
They understood the outskirts of Medina.

00:38:23.500 --> 00:38:24.500
The path.

00:38:24.500 --> 00:38:25.500
The roads.

00:38:25.500 --> 00:38:29.500
And they also started gathering how Quraysh move.

00:38:29.500 --> 00:38:30.500
The movements.

00:38:30.500 --> 00:38:32.500
How much they take when they go.

00:38:32.500 --> 00:38:33.500
When they come and so on.

00:38:33.500 --> 00:38:35.500
All this was intelligence being gathered.

00:38:35.500 --> 00:38:40.500
A lot of benefit by these little platoons that were going out.

00:38:40.500 --> 00:38:47.500
We have then the first time that Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wa sallam himself went out.

00:38:47.500 --> 00:38:49.500
Was in the month of Safar.

00:38:49.500 --> 00:38:51.500
In the second year of Hijra.

00:38:51.500 --> 00:38:54.500
He went out what was known as Ghazwa.

00:38:54.500 --> 00:38:57.500
Ghazwa is like a skirmish or a battle.

00:38:57.500 --> 00:39:00.500
It could refer to a battle if there is fighting that takes place.

00:39:00.500 --> 00:39:01.500
Sometimes it's just a skirmish.

00:39:01.500 --> 00:39:04.500
Because the two armies may not have fought.

00:39:04.500 --> 00:39:07.500
Or the two parties may not have actually clashed.

00:39:07.500 --> 00:39:09.500
So Ghazwa al-Abuwa.

00:39:09.500 --> 00:39:17.500
That's the name of the first group of army men that Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wa sallam went with.

00:39:17.500 --> 00:39:19.500
He prepared this army and he walked with them.

00:39:19.500 --> 00:39:21.500
He went with them as their leader.

00:39:21.500 --> 00:39:25.500
And it was also referred to in some books as Al-Widdan.

00:39:25.500 --> 00:39:26.500
Ghazwa al-Widdan.

00:39:26.500 --> 00:39:29.500
So al-Abuwa, you hear the name and you also hear the name Widdan.

00:39:29.500 --> 00:39:31.500
In Safar, the second year of Hijra.

00:39:31.500 --> 00:39:34.500
The Prophet sallallahu alaihi wa sallam took 70 men.

00:39:34.500 --> 00:39:37.500
All of them from amongst the Muhajireen.

00:39:37.500 --> 00:39:41.500
And he also aimed for Quraysh and the caravan that was coming back.

00:39:41.500 --> 00:39:45.500
But he had not met the caravan.

00:39:45.500 --> 00:39:47.500
And there was no fighting that took place.

00:39:47.500 --> 00:39:49.500
He spent 15 days out.

00:39:49.500 --> 00:39:52.500
And he had had a flag that Hamza radiallahu anhu was holding.

00:39:52.500 --> 00:39:54.500
And the flag was white.

00:39:54.500 --> 00:39:56.500
And when he left Madina Munawwara,

00:39:56.500 --> 00:40:00.500
one might ask, who did he leave behind as a leader there?

00:40:00.500 --> 00:40:04.500
He left behind Sa'd ibn Ubadah radiallahu anhu the first time he went out.

00:40:04.500 --> 00:40:08.500
And that was the first participation of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wa sallam.

00:40:08.500 --> 00:40:09.500
No war had taken place.

00:40:09.500 --> 00:40:12.500
Then you have the second participation was known as Buwat.

00:40:12.500 --> 00:40:14.500
Ghazwat Buwat.

00:40:14.500 --> 00:40:16.500
The reason I'm making mention of all this,

00:40:16.500 --> 00:40:19.500
many of us think that Badr was the first war.

00:40:19.500 --> 00:40:22.500
The reality is no, there were so many skirmishes before that.

00:40:22.500 --> 00:40:24.500
And one thing led to another.

00:40:24.500 --> 00:40:28.500
And the battle of Badr was only after certain things had happened.

00:40:28.500 --> 00:40:30.500
And how did they happen?

00:40:30.500 --> 00:40:32.500
We will come to it inshallah in a few moments.

00:40:32.500 --> 00:40:36.500
You have Buwat in Rabi' al-Awwal, second year of Hijra.

00:40:36.500 --> 00:40:40.500
Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wa sallam went out with 200 men.

00:40:40.500 --> 00:40:45.500
And Umayyah ibn Khalaf was coming back from Ash-Sham with 100 men.

00:40:45.500 --> 00:40:48.500
But sadly, they had already passed the caravan.

00:40:48.500 --> 00:40:49.500
So they learnt a lot.

00:40:49.500 --> 00:40:51.500
They went to these areas.

00:40:51.500 --> 00:40:52.500
They met the people.

00:40:52.500 --> 00:40:54.500
Every time they were coming back.

00:40:54.500 --> 00:40:56.500
Like the first one Al-Abuwaa,

00:40:56.500 --> 00:40:59.500
when the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wa sallam was coming back,

00:40:59.500 --> 00:41:01.500
he took a lot of time to visit the tribes,

00:41:01.500 --> 00:41:05.500
to visit the people, to meet them, to spread the word.

00:41:05.500 --> 00:41:06.500
Some may enter Islam.

00:41:06.500 --> 00:41:08.500
But more importantly,

00:41:08.500 --> 00:41:14.500
a lot of peace treaties were agreed upon between the parties.

00:41:14.500 --> 00:41:17.500
Because what you find when there is peace,

00:41:17.500 --> 00:41:20.500
thereafter, Islam spreads.

00:41:20.500 --> 00:41:23.500
And in this particular case, there was so much peace.

00:41:23.500 --> 00:41:25.500
So many of these little clans and groups

00:41:25.500 --> 00:41:28.500
started joining the forces with the Muslimin

00:41:28.500 --> 00:41:30.500
and pledging allegiance to them,

00:41:30.500 --> 00:41:35.500
especially a peace treaty that was struck between the parties.

00:41:35.500 --> 00:41:40.500
Then what had happened is something known as

00:41:40.500 --> 00:41:42.500
Ghazwa to Badrin al-Sughra.

00:41:42.500 --> 00:41:45.500
The battle of Badr, but the small one, the minor one.

00:41:45.500 --> 00:41:48.500
It's not the main battle that we all know.

00:41:48.500 --> 00:41:52.500
It was a skirmish in a place known as Safwan.

00:41:52.500 --> 00:41:54.500
And this place, what had happened is

00:41:54.500 --> 00:41:56.500
the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wa sallam in Rabi' al-Awwal

00:41:56.500 --> 00:41:57.500
in the second year of Hijra,

00:41:57.500 --> 00:41:59.500
went out with 70 men.

00:41:59.500 --> 00:42:01.500
And why did he go out?

00:42:01.500 --> 00:42:02.500
Very important.

00:42:02.500 --> 00:42:05.500
There was a man called Karz ibn Jabir al-Fihri.

00:42:05.500 --> 00:42:09.500
He had come in with a few men to Medina Munawwara.

00:42:09.500 --> 00:42:11.500
And he went into the farms,

00:42:11.500 --> 00:42:13.500
and he stole some of the sheep,

00:42:13.500 --> 00:42:16.500
and he stole a little bit of the property,

00:42:16.500 --> 00:42:17.500
and he was rushing back.

00:42:17.500 --> 00:42:18.500
When he rushed back,

00:42:18.500 --> 00:42:20.500
announcement was made in Medina

00:42:20.500 --> 00:42:21.500
that this is what happened.

00:42:21.500 --> 00:42:23.500
The Prophet sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:42:23.500 --> 00:42:25.500
gathered 70 men,

00:42:25.500 --> 00:42:27.500
and he went after this man

00:42:27.500 --> 00:42:29.500
in order to retrieve and to get back

00:42:29.500 --> 00:42:32.500
what he had stolen from Medina Munawwara.

00:42:32.500 --> 00:42:35.500
So this was the reason why he had gone.

00:42:35.500 --> 00:42:38.500
And they had gone to this place of Safwan

00:42:38.500 --> 00:42:40.500
which was very, very close to Badr.

00:42:40.500 --> 00:42:42.500
In fact, it is also called a part of Badr.

00:42:42.500 --> 00:42:44.500
And when he got there, subhanallah,

00:42:45.500 --> 00:42:47.500
this person had already skirmished,

00:42:47.500 --> 00:42:48.500
and he had run away,

00:42:48.500 --> 00:42:50.500
and there was nothing much that could have happened.

00:42:50.500 --> 00:42:54.500
But the beauty is the area of Badr was already seen.

00:42:54.500 --> 00:42:57.500
And everything that happens around it was already known.

00:42:57.500 --> 00:42:59.500
So when they went to Badr after that,

00:42:59.500 --> 00:43:02.500
they already had known what Badr was all about,

00:43:02.500 --> 00:43:06.500
and they were acquainted with a lot of the areas close to Badr.

00:43:06.500 --> 00:43:11.500
And then we had a war

00:43:12.500 --> 00:43:14.500
where the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:43:14.500 --> 00:43:16.500
took part in which was known as Dhi al-Ashirah.

00:43:16.500 --> 00:43:18.500
And this Dhi al-Ashirah was in Rabi' al-Awwal

00:43:18.500 --> 00:43:21.500
in the second year of Hijra.

00:43:21.500 --> 00:43:23.500
The Prophet sallallahu alaihi wa sallam,

00:43:23.500 --> 00:43:28.500
in fact, they had intended to gather information

00:43:28.500 --> 00:43:34.500
of the caravan of Quraysh that was heading north.

00:43:34.500 --> 00:43:36.500
And they found that they had missed it.

00:43:36.500 --> 00:43:39.500
They calculated when it would return.

00:43:39.500 --> 00:43:44.500
This caravan of Abu Sufyan.

00:43:44.500 --> 00:43:47.500
And what they did is, on its return,

00:43:47.500 --> 00:43:51.500
this is when the major battle took place.

00:43:51.500 --> 00:43:54.500
So they calculated, we missed it going up,

00:43:54.500 --> 00:43:56.500
but when it comes back, we're going to get it.

00:43:56.500 --> 00:44:00.500
Why? Because what it had in it was a lot.

00:44:00.500 --> 00:44:03.500
They had a lot of merchandise,

00:44:03.500 --> 00:44:07.500
so much that the Muslims did not want to lose out

00:44:07.500 --> 00:44:10.500
on what was rightfully theirs, subhanallah.

00:44:10.500 --> 00:44:13.500
It was returning what was theirs to them.

00:44:13.500 --> 00:44:15.500
So the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:44:15.500 --> 00:44:17.500
thereafter prepared an army.

00:44:17.500 --> 00:44:19.500
And that would be the army

00:44:19.500 --> 00:44:22.500
which finally took part in the battle

00:44:22.500 --> 00:44:24.500
known as the Battle of Badr,

00:44:24.500 --> 00:44:25.500
the main battle that we all know.

00:44:25.500 --> 00:44:28.500
But before we get to that particular battle,

00:44:28.500 --> 00:44:29.500
there were two or three things

00:44:29.500 --> 00:44:30.500
that happened in Medina Munawwara.

00:44:30.500 --> 00:44:34.500
One is, before the Battle of Badr,

00:44:34.500 --> 00:44:37.500
the direction of the Qibla changed.

00:44:37.500 --> 00:44:40.500
So Allah instructed His Messenger sallallahu alaihi wa sallam,

00:44:40.500 --> 00:44:43.500
16 months, 16 to 17 months

00:44:43.500 --> 00:44:45.500
after he had come to Medina Munawwara,

00:44:45.500 --> 00:44:49.500
that we are seeing that you are looking

00:44:49.500 --> 00:44:51.500
for the direction in prayer

00:44:51.500 --> 00:44:53.500
and we are instructing you

00:44:53.500 --> 00:44:56.500
to now face Mecca al-Mukarramah.

00:44:56.500 --> 00:44:59.500
So at that juncture, the verses were revealed.

00:44:59.500 --> 00:45:06.500
فَوَلِّ وَجَهَكَ شَطُرَ الْمَسْجِدِ الْحَرَامِ

00:45:06.500 --> 00:45:10.500
Turn your face towards al-Masjid al-Haram

00:45:10.500 --> 00:45:12.500
in Mecca al-Mukarramah.

00:45:12.500 --> 00:45:14.500
And the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:45:14.500 --> 00:45:16.500
made the Qibla.

00:45:16.500 --> 00:45:18.500
It was almost, if you go to Medina Munawwara,

00:45:18.500 --> 00:45:20.500
it's almost 180 degrees.

00:45:20.500 --> 00:45:22.500
So it's like a straight line.

00:45:22.500 --> 00:45:23.500
If you're facing this way,

00:45:23.500 --> 00:45:24.500
you now face the other way.

00:45:24.500 --> 00:45:26.500
Almost 180.

00:45:26.500 --> 00:45:30.500
So he had made the Mimbar in the other direction.

00:45:30.500 --> 00:45:32.500
What happened to the old Mimbar?

00:45:32.500 --> 00:45:34.500
That area was given a little bit of a roof

00:45:34.500 --> 00:45:37.500
and it was raised slightly

00:45:37.500 --> 00:45:40.500
and it was known as al-Suffah.

00:45:40.500 --> 00:45:43.500
Al-Suffah meaning an area where the poor

00:45:43.500 --> 00:45:45.500
and those who don't have much,

00:45:45.500 --> 00:45:46.500
those who don't have a place to go,

00:45:46.500 --> 00:45:49.500
all the Muhajireen who were still coming in,

00:45:49.500 --> 00:45:51.500
they would actually settle there for a while

00:45:51.500 --> 00:45:54.500
and stay and spend a lot of their time in Ibadah

00:45:54.500 --> 00:45:56.500
and learning the religion and sacrificing

00:45:56.500 --> 00:45:57.500
for the pleasure of Allah.

00:45:57.500 --> 00:45:59.500
InshaAllah, we will get to that at some stage,

00:45:59.500 --> 00:46:01.500
but this area was known as al-Suffah.

00:46:01.500 --> 00:46:03.500
It now became the back of the Masjid,

00:46:03.500 --> 00:46:05.500
yet it used to be the front of the Masjid

00:46:05.500 --> 00:46:08.500
when the Qibla was in the other direction.

00:46:08.500 --> 00:46:11.500
So this is one thing that had happened.

00:46:11.500 --> 00:46:13.500
One of the beauties

00:46:13.500 --> 00:46:15.500
or one of the beautiful points

00:46:15.500 --> 00:46:18.500
of the changing of the Qibla was that

00:46:18.500 --> 00:46:21.500
the Muslims wanted to liberate

00:46:21.500 --> 00:46:24.500
their own home city of Makkah.

00:46:24.500 --> 00:46:25.500
It was their city.

00:46:25.500 --> 00:46:26.500
Most of them were born in there.

00:46:26.500 --> 00:46:28.500
The Muhajireen, almost all of them,

00:46:28.500 --> 00:46:31.500
besides a few, were born in Makkah.

00:46:31.500 --> 00:46:33.500
And now they were facing Makkah.

00:46:33.500 --> 00:46:35.500
Allah explained to them

00:46:35.500 --> 00:46:38.500
the value of this house of Makkah

00:46:38.500 --> 00:46:39.500
a four time.

00:46:39.500 --> 00:46:41.500
And now they were facing that direction.

00:46:41.500 --> 00:46:44.500
How could they face the direction

00:46:44.500 --> 00:46:47.500
of a place that is in the hands of their enemies?

00:46:47.500 --> 00:46:49.500
So it gave them all the more reason

00:46:49.500 --> 00:46:51.500
to want to go and be victorious

00:46:51.500 --> 00:46:53.500
in Makkah al-Mukarramah.

00:46:53.500 --> 00:46:55.500
You see how Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:46:55.500 --> 00:46:58.500
made their hearts incline towards going back

00:46:58.500 --> 00:47:00.500
and getting whatever belonged to them.

00:47:00.500 --> 00:47:01.500
Subhanallah.

00:47:01.500 --> 00:47:03.500
So this was one of the reasons

00:47:03.500 --> 00:47:04.500
or one of the benefits

00:47:04.500 --> 00:47:06.500
of the change of the Qibla.

00:47:06.500 --> 00:47:09.500
After that, in the same year in Sha'ban,

00:47:09.500 --> 00:47:11.500
fasting was prescribed.

00:47:11.500 --> 00:47:12.500
O you who believe,

00:47:12.500 --> 00:47:14.500
fasting is prescribed upon you in the same way

00:47:14.500 --> 00:47:16.500
it was prescribed upon those before you

00:47:16.500 --> 00:47:18.500
in order that you may achieve piety.

00:47:18.500 --> 00:47:19.500
Verses were revealed.

00:47:19.500 --> 00:47:21.500
And Masha'Allah,

00:47:21.500 --> 00:47:23.500
in the month of Ramadan,

00:47:23.500 --> 00:47:25.500
they fasted for the first time.

00:47:25.500 --> 00:47:27.500
And in the same month of Ramadan,

00:47:27.500 --> 00:47:29.500
the battle of Badr took place

00:47:29.500 --> 00:47:31.500
in the month of Ramadan.

00:47:31.500 --> 00:47:34.500
14 years after being driven out of their homes,

00:47:34.500 --> 00:47:36.500
17th of.

00:47:36.500 --> 00:47:39.500
In fact, 14 years after revelation

00:47:39.500 --> 00:47:41.500
and prophethood,

00:47:41.500 --> 00:47:44.500
you now find these people were

00:47:44.500 --> 00:47:47.500
given the opportunity to face those

00:47:47.500 --> 00:47:49.500
who had persecuted them for so long.

00:47:49.500 --> 00:47:52.500
Also, what was made compulsory in the same year

00:47:52.500 --> 00:47:53.500
was Sadaqatul Fitr,

00:47:53.500 --> 00:47:55.500
what we know when we are

00:47:55.500 --> 00:47:57.500
opening our fast

00:47:57.500 --> 00:47:59.500
at the end of Ramadan.

00:47:59.500 --> 00:48:00.500
And we need to give out

00:48:00.500 --> 00:48:02.500
what is known as the Fitr

00:48:02.500 --> 00:48:03.500
that was made,

00:48:03.500 --> 00:48:05.500
it was prescribed also

00:48:05.500 --> 00:48:07.500
in the second year of Hijra.

00:48:07.500 --> 00:48:10.500
And Zakah became compulsory

00:48:10.500 --> 00:48:13.500
just after the month of Ramadan.

00:48:13.500 --> 00:48:15.500
This battle of Badr,

00:48:15.500 --> 00:48:17.500
the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:48:17.500 --> 00:48:19.500
sent Talhah ibn Ubaydillah

00:48:19.500 --> 00:48:20.500
and Sa'id ibn Zaid

00:48:20.500 --> 00:48:21.500
towards the north,

00:48:21.500 --> 00:48:24.500
in order to gather information

00:48:24.500 --> 00:48:27.500
of the caravan of Abu Sufyan

00:48:27.500 --> 00:48:28.500
that had gone up north.

00:48:28.500 --> 00:48:30.500
And these people,

00:48:30.500 --> 00:48:32.500
they passed by Abu Sufyan

00:48:32.500 --> 00:48:34.500
and they saw him.

00:48:34.500 --> 00:48:35.500
So they quickly sent a message

00:48:35.500 --> 00:48:37.500
to Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:48:37.500 --> 00:48:38.500
in Madina Munawwarah,

00:48:38.500 --> 00:48:39.500
saying,

00:48:39.500 --> 00:48:41.500
this man is on his return,

00:48:41.500 --> 00:48:43.500
he is now coming back

00:48:43.500 --> 00:48:46.500
with him are forty men,

00:48:46.500 --> 00:48:48.500
one thousand camels

00:48:48.500 --> 00:48:50.500
and fifty thousand dinars,

00:48:50.500 --> 00:48:52.500
which means he has a lot,

00:48:52.500 --> 00:48:53.500
Subhanallah.

00:48:53.500 --> 00:48:54.500
He has so much

00:48:54.500 --> 00:48:56.500
and a lot of merchandise.

00:48:56.500 --> 00:48:57.500
So the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:48:57.500 --> 00:48:58.500
made an announcement

00:48:58.500 --> 00:49:00.500
in Madina Munawwarah.

00:49:00.500 --> 00:49:01.500
And that announcement was,

00:49:01.500 --> 00:49:03.500
who is ready to go out

00:49:03.500 --> 00:49:06.500
in order to face Quraysh,

00:49:06.500 --> 00:49:07.500
they are coming back

00:49:07.500 --> 00:49:08.500
with their caravan

00:49:08.500 --> 00:49:10.500
and we are going to face them.

00:49:10.500 --> 00:49:12.500
At that particular time,

00:49:12.500 --> 00:49:14.500
it was not compulsory

00:49:14.500 --> 00:49:16.500
for all of them to go out,

00:49:16.500 --> 00:49:18.500
just like they went to face

00:49:18.500 --> 00:49:20.500
the previous caravans

00:49:20.500 --> 00:49:21.500
where they were not

00:49:21.500 --> 00:49:22.500
really very successful.

00:49:22.500 --> 00:49:24.500
This was also one of those.

00:49:24.500 --> 00:49:25.500
They did not intend

00:49:25.500 --> 00:49:26.500
a full-fledged war.

00:49:26.500 --> 00:49:28.500
They only intended

00:49:28.500 --> 00:49:30.500
to get part of the merchandise

00:49:30.500 --> 00:49:31.500
from the caravan

00:49:31.500 --> 00:49:32.500
that was returning.

00:49:32.500 --> 00:49:34.500
And so you find people

00:49:34.500 --> 00:49:36.500
started giving their names

00:49:36.500 --> 00:49:39.500
and people were being vetted.

00:49:39.500 --> 00:49:40.500
What is the meaning of vetted?

00:49:40.500 --> 00:49:41.500
Vetted meaning,

00:49:41.500 --> 00:49:42.500
some people are known

00:49:42.500 --> 00:49:43.500
that this person's condition is good,

00:49:43.500 --> 00:49:44.500
he can come.

00:49:44.500 --> 00:49:45.500
Some people,

00:49:45.500 --> 00:49:47.500
they had certain matters

00:49:47.500 --> 00:49:48.500
that disallowed them

00:49:48.500 --> 00:49:50.500
from joining the battle.

00:49:50.500 --> 00:49:51.500
One of them was

00:49:51.500 --> 00:49:52.500
Uthman ibn Affan,

00:49:52.500 --> 00:49:54.500
may Allah be pleased with him.

00:49:54.500 --> 00:49:57.500
He was disallowed from joining the battle

00:49:57.500 --> 00:50:00.500
because his wife was ill and sick.

00:50:00.500 --> 00:50:02.500
The daughter of Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:50:02.500 --> 00:50:03.500
Ruqayya, may Allah be pleased with her.

00:50:03.500 --> 00:50:06.500
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:50:06.500 --> 00:50:08.500
So this was a major battle,

00:50:08.500 --> 00:50:09.500
the decisive battle,

00:50:10.500 --> 00:50:12.500
the first major battle.

00:50:12.500 --> 00:50:15.500
And yet you have the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:50:15.500 --> 00:50:16.500
telling certain people

00:50:16.500 --> 00:50:18.500
that go back and serve your parents.

00:50:18.500 --> 00:50:19.500
And certain people go back

00:50:19.500 --> 00:50:20.500
and serve your,

00:50:20.500 --> 00:50:22.500
meaning look after your family members.

00:50:22.500 --> 00:50:24.500
Because that is compulsory

00:50:24.500 --> 00:50:26.500
upon you as a person.

00:50:26.500 --> 00:50:27.500
And this here,

00:50:27.500 --> 00:50:29.500
it's compulsory upon us collectively.

00:50:29.500 --> 00:50:30.500
So if some of us go,

00:50:30.500 --> 00:50:32.500
the rest of us will not be penalized.

00:50:32.500 --> 00:50:34.500
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:50:34.500 --> 00:50:35.500
a deep understanding.

00:50:35.500 --> 00:50:36.500
The statement I have made

00:50:36.500 --> 00:50:37.500
is very important.

00:50:37.500 --> 00:50:39.500
We learn from this

00:50:39.500 --> 00:50:41.500
that Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:50:41.500 --> 00:50:43.500
had a system in place

00:50:43.500 --> 00:50:45.500
from Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:50:45.500 --> 00:50:47.500
And it worked like clockwork.

00:50:47.500 --> 00:50:49.500
And it resulted in the fact

00:50:49.500 --> 00:50:52.500
that today we are sitting in this masjid.

00:50:52.500 --> 00:50:53.500
Subhanallah.

00:50:53.500 --> 00:50:54.500
So insha'Allah we will be going through

00:50:54.500 --> 00:50:56.500
the Battle of Badr in detail

00:50:56.500 --> 00:50:57.500
starting from tomorrow.

00:50:57.500 --> 00:50:59.500
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:50:59.500 --> 00:51:00.500
to grant us benefit

00:51:00.500 --> 00:51:01.500
until we meet again.

00:51:01.500 --> 00:51:02.500
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:51:02.500 --> 00:51:04.500
bless our prophet Muhammad.

00:51:04.500 --> 00:51:05.500
Subhanallah, praise be to Allah.

00:51:05.500 --> 00:51:06.500
Subhanaka Allahumma, praise be to you.

00:51:06.500 --> 00:51:08.500
We bear witness that there is no god but you.

00:51:08.500 --> 00:51:09.500
We seek your forgiveness

00:51:09.500 --> 00:51:10.500
and repent to you.
